{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014Y99G7YYCmLYqyNu3PnFUh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to understand the Elasticsearch pods and how they're configured. The task says:\n- Configure secure settings so Elasticsearch can authenticate to MinIO.\n- Register a snapshot repository named \"minio-repo\" and create one successful snapshot.\n- Credentials are stored in the Secret \"es-secure-settings\" (but this doesn't exist yet!)\n- Do not place credentials in elasticsearch.yml or env vars.\n\nThe task says credentials are stored in Secret \"es-secure-settings\", but it doesn't exist. I need to:\n1. Create the \"es-secure-settings\" secret with MinIO credentials\n2. Configure Elasticsearch to use the secure keystore to pick up these credentials\n3. Register the S3/MinIO snapshot repository\n4. Create a snapshot\n\nElasticsearch uses the keystore to store secure settings, and for S3-compatible repositories like MinIO, I need the `repository-s3` plugin installed with credentials stored as `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key`. Let me check what plugins are already installed in the ES pods and how the StatefulSet is configured.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1197,"cache_read_input_tokens":29862,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1197},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56882c1f-681b-4a3c-bf52-fdec7cd44518","uuid":"ba417065-1d40-4336-97e5-5b771fff5577","request_id":"req_011CcLfp61tosSe6NzWrahD6"}
