{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RPiKLuxTCytDit5vfeircN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"MinIO is reachable. Now I need to configure the Elasticsearch keystore with the S3 credentials. The proper way to do this without restarting pods (using the Elasticsearch `_nodes/reload_secure_settings` API) is:\n\n1. Add the credentials to the keystore on each ES node using the `elasticsearch-keystore` command\n2. Call `POST /_nodes/reload_secure_settings` to reload them without restart\n\nBut wait - the keystore is a file on disk, and since the data volumes are `emptyDir`, restarting pods would lose the keystore anyway. So I need to either:\n- Mount the keystore from a secret/configmap, or\n- Add the keystore entries on running pods and reload via API\n\nFor the second approach, I'll need to add `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` to the keystore on all five nodes, then trigger a reload through the API. I can do this by piping the credential values into the keystore add command on each pod, then calling the reload endpoint.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":250,"cache_read_input_tokens":38518,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":250},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56882c1f-681b-4a3c-bf52-fdec7cd44518","uuid":"a774e6a6-5947-41c3-8e26-ffec05076345","request_id":"req_011CcLfvs8SPcwoPQGKidPt5"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RPiKLuxTCytDit5vfeircN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"MinIO is reachable. Now I'll add S3 credentials to the keystore on all Elasticsearch nodes and reload without restarting:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":250,"cache_read_input_tokens":38518,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":250},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56882c1f-681b-4a3c-bf52-fdec7cd44518","uuid":"6f5decc3-d090-45a2-b06d-fd31259106d0","request_id":"req_011CcLfvs8SPcwoPQGKidPt5"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RPiKLuxTCytDit5vfeircN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XGBscftsPnvSyrk1CTFoZp","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"ACCESS_KEY=\"minioadmin\"\nSECRET_KEY=\"minioadmin\"\n\nfor pod in es-0 es-1 es-2 es-data-0 es-data-1; do\n  echo \"=== Configuring keystore on $pod ===\"\n  kubectl exec -n elasticsearch $pod -- bash -c \"\n    echo '${ACCESS_KEY}' | elasticsearch-keystore add --stdin s3.client.default.access_key --force\n    echo '${SECRET_KEY}' | elasticsearch-keystore add --stdin s3.client.default.secret_key --force\n    elasticsearch-keystore list\n  \" 2>&1 | grep -v \"^Defaulted\"\ndone","description":"Add MinIO credentials to Elasticsearch keystore on all nodes"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":250,"cache_read_input_tokens":38518,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":250},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56882c1f-681b-4a3c-bf52-fdec7cd44518","uuid":"e7886834-99bc-4ab4-a10c-0f73c828a0eb","request_id":"req_011CcLfvs8SPcwoPQGKidPt5"}
