{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012CmZsGdBmz6v5YkTcK1LSY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is confirmed. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Root causes fixed:**\n1. **Missing MinIO service** — the `minio-init` job failed because no `minio` Service existed yet, so `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` didn't resolve. Created a ClusterIP service exposing port 9000.\n2. **Missing bucket** — since the init job failed, the `es-backups` bucket didn't exist. Created it via `mc mb` inside the MinIO pod.\n3. **No S3 credentials in keystore** — Elasticsearch needs `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` in its secure keystore (not in `elasticsearch.yml` or env vars).\n\n**Actions taken (no pod restarts required):**\n- Created `es-secure-settings` Secret with MinIO credentials (`minioadmin`/`minioadmin`)\n- Added `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` to the Elasticsearch keystore on all 5 nodes using `elasticsearch-keystore add --stdin`\n- Called `POST /_nodes/reload_secure_settings` — all 5 nodes acknowledged\n- Registered the `minio-repo` S3 repository pointing to `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000`, bucket `es-backups`, HTTP protocol, path-style access\n- Created `snapshot-1` which completed with `state: SUCCESS` in 1.6 seconds, capturing 1 shard with 0 failures"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":991,"cache_read_input_tokens":48221,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":991},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56882c1f-681b-4a3c-bf52-fdec7cd44518","uuid":"07e2a19f-a19d-4639-b99e-5fcc46b30241","request_id":"req_011CcLg5edcWCtVf7UG4s61f"}
